Prof. Liu received his B.S., M.S. and Ph.D. degrees from Electronic Engineering Department, Tsinghua
University in 1999, 2002, and 2007. He worked as a Research Assistant in Circuit and System
Divisions in Tsinghua University from 2002 to 2004. (Referred to CV) His main research interests
include: Embedded System, Nonvolatile Computing, Electronics Design Automation and Power/Thermal
Aware VLSI Design and Test.  Our group currently focuses on High Performance Low Power circuit
device, chip architecture and system design methodology on next generation computing applications,
specifically including the following fields:

-  [Ultra Low Power Circuit, Architecture and Protocol for Wireless Sensor Node][Link1]
-  Nonvolatile Computing
-  Novel Design Techniques for Embedded Systems
-  Power Efficient Architecture (Heterogeneous MPSoC) for Software Defined Radio
-  Thermal Aware MPSoC Design and Test


[link1]:      http://jekyllrb.com

